1
00:00:44,457 --> 00:00:48,496
- Ally, can we get a recap?
- Remember the Kowolskis?

2
00:00:48,577 --> 00:00:52,729
They want to set a record by
making Buffalo's largest cookie.

3
00:00:52,817 --> 00:00:54,694
- You have to wear this.
- A hairnet?

4
00:00:54,777 --> 00:00:58,690
Health Department. If you're around
the cookie, you have to have it on.

5
00:00:58,777 --> 00:01:00,096
I just did the hair.

6
00:01:00,177 --> 00:01:01,496
The hairis perfect.

7
00:01:01,577 --> 00:01:03,693
All right, give it to me.

8
00:01:05,697 --> 00:01:09,053
God... why do you hate me?

9
00:01:09,137 --> 00:01:11,776
We're rolling. And speed.

10
00:01:11,857 --> 00:01:14,530
For three decades,
the Kowolski Bakery

11
00:01:14,617 --> 00:01:17,415
has been a mainstay
in downtown Buffalo,

12
00:01:17,497 --> 00:01:21,046
known for their sinfully sweet,
cream-filled Polski pierogies

13
00:01:21,137 --> 00:01:24,925
and the occasional
sugar-induced coma that follows.

14
00:01:25,017 --> 00:01:27,736
Today, in honour of their 30th anniversary,

15
00:01:27,817 --> 00:01:31,571
they've invited us to ride along
as they go for the record

16
00:01:32,257 --> 00:01:34,487
on Buffalo's biggest cookie.

17
00:01:37,057 --> 00:01:40,811
Vol. Do you need
a tissue or something?

18
00:01:40,897 --> 00:01:43,457
Can we get Vol a tissue? Or a spoon?

19
00:01:43,537 --> 00:01:45,334
Good thing we're wearing these.

20
00:01:45,417 --> 00:01:48,648
I wouldn't want any stray hairs
to fall into the booger.

21
00:01:48,737 --> 00:01:51,410
- We doing this again?
- No. We can cut to B roll.

22
00:01:51,497 --> 00:01:52,725
Moving on!

23
00:01:52,817 --> 00:01:57,015
Tell me, Mama,
why make Buffalo's biggest cookie?

24
00:01:57,497 --> 00:02:04,175
Well, man from Health Department
say he find rat pellet in our pastry.

25
00:02:04,257 --> 00:02:08,489
But I say no, is big chocolate sprinkle.

26
00:02:08,577 --> 00:02:11,216
But he shut store down.

27
00:02:11,377 --> 00:02:13,732
So we clean up,

28
00:02:13,817 --> 00:02:17,890
make big cookie
for to bring customers back.

29
00:02:19,177 --> 00:02:21,133
Well, I admire your candour.

30
00:02:21,217 --> 00:02:23,014
Let's try that again, shall we?

31
00:02:23,097 --> 00:02:26,976
Tell me, Mama,
why make Buffalo's biggest cookie?

32
00:02:27,737 --> 00:02:32,015
So the children of the neighbourhood
will be happy.

33
00:02:32,097 --> 00:02:35,646
It must be wonderful seeing
the smiles on their little faces.

34
00:02:36,857 --> 00:02:39,246
I work in back. I see no smiles.

35
00:02:42,337 --> 00:02:46,455
The previous record was 8 feet
7 inches, baked by Gladys Pelsnick.

36
00:02:46,537 --> 00:02:49,415
If this cookie beats that, it will prove

37
00:02:49,497 --> 00:02:51,647
the Kowolskis
have much more free time.

38
00:02:51,737 --> 00:02:55,366
And the cookie is... 10 feet, 4 inches!

39
00:02:55,457 --> 00:02:58,017
We have a new record!

40
00:02:58,617 --> 00:03:01,290
Cue the cheesy inspirational music!

41
00:03:18,337 --> 00:03:20,646
But what are we really looking at here?

42
00:03:20,737 --> 00:03:22,534
Is it just a big cookie?

43
00:03:22,617 --> 00:03:25,654
Or does this cookie represent
the pride of Buffalo?

44
00:03:25,737 --> 00:03:28,968
Its hard-working citizens
the key ingredient -

45
00:03:29,057 --> 00:03:31,048
with a few nuts thrown in.

46
00:03:31,937 --> 00:03:34,053
And finally,
the love of our families,

47
00:03:34,137 --> 00:03:36,776
which provides the warm centre,

48
00:03:36,857 --> 00:03:41,135
making our beloved Buffalo
the sweetest place to live.

49
00:03:41,217 --> 00:03:43,970
And that's the way
the cookie crumbles.

50
00:03:44,057 --> 00:03:46,969
I'm Bruce Nolan, Eyewitness News.

51
00:03:47,937 --> 00:03:49,928
And cut.

52
00:03:50,697 --> 00:03:52,574
So what do you think?

53
00:03:52,657 --> 00:03:54,056
It's really good.

54
00:03:54,137 --> 00:03:56,697
It sucks. It's a story about a cookie.

55
00:03:56,777 --> 00:03:59,974
The Pillsbury Doughboy
would be riveted.

56
00:04:00,057 --> 00:04:04,289
It made me laugh. Nothing wrong
with making people laugh.

57
00:04:04,377 --> 00:04:07,926
I'll never be an anchorman.
The job's there, but I can't reach it.

58
00:04:08,017 --> 00:04:12,807
Every time they make me do
this kind of stuff I have to act like a goof.

59
00:04:12,897 --> 00:04:16,207
I have no credibility. Not good.

60
00:04:16,297 --> 00:04:18,572
- Now you just sound silly.
- Forget it.

61
00:04:18,657 --> 00:04:22,172
It's not important.
Let's watch it one more time.

62
00:04:22,297 --> 00:04:24,208
- No.
- Once more? Please?

63
00:04:24,297 --> 00:04:27,687
No! You promised to help me
with this photo album.

64
00:04:28,777 --> 00:04:30,893
Now get your gooy butt over here.

65
00:04:35,337 --> 00:04:37,328
Looking.

66
00:04:37,937 --> 00:04:38,926
OK.

67
00:04:39,017 --> 00:04:42,976
Just go through this stack
and pick your favourites.

68
00:04:47,657 --> 00:04:49,454
Come on. This is fun, right?

69
00:04:49,537 --> 00:04:51,528
Isn't this fun? This is nice.

70
00:04:52,497 --> 00:04:54,408
Evan's going to get that anchor job.

71
00:04:54,497 --> 00:04:56,089
- Bruce!
- He's the favourite.

72
00:04:56,177 --> 00:04:59,806
You know what? Just forget it.
This is just our life.

73
00:04:59,897 --> 00:05:02,855
We can always just
have some kid do it for us.

74
00:05:03,617 --> 00:05:05,369
Hold the phone.

75
00:05:05,457 --> 00:05:07,925
I like this one.
Our weekend at the lake.

76
00:05:08,017 --> 00:05:10,929
That's supposed to be in our private stash.

77
00:05:11,017 --> 00:05:14,248
- You look perky. Must have been cold.
- Give it to me.

78
00:05:14,337 --> 00:05:16,692
I think I'll put this on my computer.

79
00:05:16,777 --> 00:05:18,733
- Give it to me. Come on.
- No!

80
00:05:18,817 --> 00:05:20,887
Fine. Do with it what you will.

81
00:05:20,977 --> 00:05:22,649
I don't care.

82
00:05:22,737 --> 00:05:25,126
- I will do with it what I will.
- Jesus.

83
00:05:27,177 --> 00:05:29,407
I might even send this in to Playboy.

84
00:05:29,497 --> 00:05:33,251
- Their layouts can be quite tasteful.
- Give that to me right now!

85
00:05:34,217 --> 00:05:36,208
- Rough stuff.
- I'm going to hurt you.

86
00:05:41,737 --> 00:05:43,853
Sweetie? Time to get up.

87
00:05:46,297 --> 00:05:48,288
Good dream. No.

88
00:05:57,617 --> 00:06:02,088
The Buffalo Sabres lost again last
night to the Toronto Maple Leafs.

89
00:06:02,177 --> 00:06:04,532
Of course they did. They're my team.

90
00:06:04,857 --> 00:06:06,848
That's the way the cookie crumbles.

91
00:06:06,937 --> 00:06:09,815
There might be something
to this cookie line.

92
00:06:09,897 --> 00:06:15,290
The greatest anchors have a signature
sign-off. Like Walter Cronkite.

93
00:06:17,177 --> 00:06:19,372
And that's the way it was.

94
00:06:19,457 --> 00:06:22,654
That's the way the cookie crumbles.

95
00:06:22,737 --> 00:06:27,094
That's the way I like it

96
00:06:28,217 --> 00:06:29,570
Oh, no.

97
00:06:29,657 --> 00:06:32,171
- Grace, the dog!
- I'm in the shower!

98
00:06:36,937 --> 00:06:38,609
No, Sam. Bad dog.

99
00:06:38,697 --> 00:06:40,927
Inside, bad. Outside, good.

100
00:06:47,737 --> 00:06:49,728
You're done now. Great.

101
00:06:50,777 --> 00:06:53,450
B- E-A-utiful.

102
00:06:55,177 --> 00:06:57,816
Come on.
Let's go back in and have a shit.

103
00:07:03,057 --> 00:07:06,015
- What is the dillio?
- We are having a blood drive.

104
00:07:06,977 --> 00:07:09,332
- Needles. Yuck.
- They need my blood.

105
00:07:09,417 --> 00:07:12,693
I have a very rare blood type.
I'm AB positive.

106
00:07:12,777 --> 00:07:14,847
Really? I'm IB positive.

107
00:07:14,937 --> 00:07:18,850
I B positive they ain't touching me
with no needle. It's just so...

108
00:07:18,937 --> 00:07:21,656
- Helpful and life-saving?
- No. It's blood.

109
00:07:21,737 --> 00:07:25,207
Blood is supposed to stay
inside the body, where it's meant to be.

110
00:07:25,297 --> 00:07:29,131
Besides, they stockpile this stuff
in a warehouse, it's all on ice,

111
00:07:29,217 --> 00:07:30,969
and they say there's a shortage.

112
00:07:31,057 --> 00:07:32,968
Where did you hear that?

113
00:07:33,057 --> 00:07:34,934
From a friend of a friend

114
00:07:35,017 --> 00:07:38,487
of a girl whose sister is going out with
someone in the government.

115
00:07:38,577 --> 00:07:40,852
For your protection,
I cannot discuss it.

116
00:07:40,937 --> 00:07:43,246
Now get out,
before they see us together.

117
00:07:47,097 --> 00:07:49,850
Here. You need these more than I do.

118
00:07:49,937 --> 00:07:51,336
What is "these"?

119
00:07:51,417 --> 00:07:53,567
Prayer beads.
The kids made them for me.

120
00:07:53,657 --> 00:07:57,445
- They will keep you safe.
- I hope they're powerful.

121
00:07:57,537 --> 00:08:00,927
I'm going to need a friggin' miracle
to get to work on time.

122
00:08:11,097 --> 00:08:14,692
This isn't happening.
Not now. Not during sweeps week.

123
00:08:18,777 --> 00:08:20,574
Oh, God.

124
00:08:21,417 --> 00:08:23,851
Yup, meeting started without me.

125
00:08:23,937 --> 00:08:26,451
This is my luck.

126
00:08:33,057 --> 00:08:35,048
Come on.

127
00:08:38,577 --> 00:08:40,568
Jesus.

128
00:08:40,697 --> 00:08:42,688
Get out of there!

129
00:08:46,657 --> 00:08:49,615
"Are you blind?" No, but I'm late.

130
00:08:51,737 --> 00:08:54,535
Is yourchild in direjeopardy?

131
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:56,608
Find out tonight after the game.

132
00:08:56,697 --> 00:08:58,369
Promos are approved.

133
00:08:58,457 --> 00:09:01,529
Jack? Shouldn't we be focusing
on Pete's retirement?

134
00:09:01,617 --> 00:09:04,973
- This is his last week.
- Any word on the anchor position?

135
00:09:05,057 --> 00:09:07,935
Evan, when I know something,
you'll know something.

136
00:09:08,737 --> 00:09:10,329
Sorry I'm late.

137
00:09:10,417 --> 00:09:12,692
Traffic was...

138
00:09:12,777 --> 00:09:14,529
Did you already play the spots?

139
00:09:14,617 --> 00:09:17,256
Nice story,
but we're going with Evan's piece.

140
00:09:17,337 --> 00:09:20,568
The sex scandal
in the mayor's office for sweeps.

141
00:09:22,017 --> 00:09:24,611
Yeah. Sweeps.

142
00:09:25,217 --> 00:09:27,447
And that's the way
the cookie crumbles.

143
00:09:29,137 --> 00:09:31,128
I'm just messing with you, Bruce.

144
00:09:31,217 --> 00:09:37,213
See, you just gotta remember that
the newsroom is like a big cookie.

145
00:09:38,937 --> 00:09:42,612
Do you like jazz, Evan?
Let me play something for you.

146
00:09:49,417 --> 00:09:52,090
- I can hold that note all day.
- Knock it off, guys.

147
00:09:52,617 --> 00:09:54,733
We'll keep your story in reserve.

148
00:09:54,817 --> 00:09:58,810
Can we get back to the board so we'll
have something to put on the air today?

149
00:09:58,897 --> 00:10:02,606
Great choice, Jack.
The Cadillac of bolognas.

150
00:10:02,697 --> 00:10:04,494
Jack, can I talk to you?

151
00:10:04,577 --> 00:10:07,137
- Sure. What do you need?
- Sweeps.

152
00:10:07,217 --> 00:10:10,926
Jack, hear me out.
I'm starting to get desperate.

153
00:10:11,057 --> 00:10:13,252
I'm pushing 40
and what have I got to show?

154
00:10:13,337 --> 00:10:17,649
I've hit a kind of ceiling. There's an
anti-Bruce barrier I can't get past.

155
00:10:17,737 --> 00:10:20,934
And Evan is loving it.

156
00:10:21,017 --> 00:10:24,805
He gets the stories, he gets on sweeps...
I should be more like Evan.

157
00:10:24,897 --> 00:10:27,013
Don't be like Evan. Evan's an asshole.

158
00:10:27,097 --> 00:10:29,816
- I can be an asshole.
- No, Bruce. You can't.

159
00:10:34,537 --> 00:10:37,176
- You going to pick that up?
- Yeah. I'm sorry.

160
00:10:37,257 --> 00:10:40,886
This anchor thing opening up
has got me nuts.

161
00:10:40,977 --> 00:10:42,968
- Hi, Susan.
- Hi, Jack.

162
00:10:45,177 --> 00:10:48,328
You're a good reporter.
You make people laugh.

163
00:10:50,097 --> 00:10:51,689
All right. I'll tell you what.

164
00:10:51,777 --> 00:10:54,928
Today is the 156th anniversary
of the Maid Of The Mist.

165
00:10:55,017 --> 00:10:59,249
- I want you in Niagara Falls in an hour.
- The Maid Of The Mist is always live.

166
00:11:00,777 --> 00:11:04,975
- Evan always does the live feeds.
- Now you and Evan get the live feeds.

167
00:11:05,057 --> 00:11:07,207
I'm going live? During sweeps?

168
00:11:07,297 --> 00:11:09,606
Watch your step.
I've seen your outtakes.

169
00:11:09,697 --> 00:11:11,574
Jack, you will not regret this.

170
00:11:12,537 --> 00:11:15,097
And I won't forget you
when I go national.

171
00:11:15,177 --> 00:11:16,769
Can you...?

172
00:11:17,777 --> 00:11:19,768
Thanks, pal.

173
00:11:19,857 --> 00:11:23,532
Can I have your wish now?
I'll put it in the wish jar.

174
00:11:23,617 --> 00:11:24,970
Put your wish in.

175
00:11:25,057 --> 00:11:27,048
- Me, too.
- Put your wish in.

176
00:11:27,537 --> 00:11:29,414
That looks like a big wish.

177
00:11:29,497 --> 00:11:32,375
No, Martin, don't eat that.

178
00:11:32,457 --> 00:11:35,369
Don't put that in your mouth.
That's paste, honey.

179
00:11:37,497 --> 00:11:40,534
- That must have tasted awful.
- Mommy!

180
00:11:42,737 --> 00:11:45,729
Did you have a good time
with Aunt Gracie today?

181
00:11:45,817 --> 00:11:50,095
- See how nice this is? Baby on the hip.
- It's amazing. You've become Mom.

182
00:11:50,177 --> 00:11:52,407
The transformation is complete.

183
00:11:53,617 --> 00:11:54,766
I'll get it.

184
00:11:54,857 --> 00:11:56,654
- Small Wonders Day Care.
- Grace?

185
00:11:56,737 --> 00:11:59,729
It's Debbie, the sister
whose life you're notwasting.

186
00:11:59,817 --> 00:12:01,933
- OK.
- Bye, Debbie!

187
00:12:02,017 --> 00:12:04,008
Hi. Sorry.

188
00:12:04,097 --> 00:12:06,975
Debbie forgot to take her meds today.
Where are you?

189
00:12:07,057 --> 00:12:09,491
A little place
called the winner's circle.

190
00:12:09,577 --> 00:12:11,693
I'm at the falls, doing a live report.

191
00:12:11,777 --> 00:12:13,688
Live? That's great!

192
00:12:13,777 --> 00:12:16,735
Yeah! It's happening, hon.
I got sweeps and I'm live.

193
00:12:16,817 --> 00:12:19,012
They're seeing if I can think on my feet.

194
00:12:19,097 --> 00:12:21,850
Like I might have to do
in a live anchor situation.

195
00:12:21,937 --> 00:12:23,529
Oh, my gosh.

196
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:27,292
Yeah! Jack practically came out
and told me.

197
00:12:27,377 --> 00:12:28,605
Practically?

198
00:12:28,697 --> 00:12:31,495
He didn't spell it out. Legally, he can't.

199
00:12:31,577 --> 00:12:35,889
This is what happened to Susan Ortega
before they bumped her up to the desk.

200
00:12:35,977 --> 00:12:38,093
It's good.

201
00:12:38,177 --> 00:12:42,170
Well, honey, I just don't want you
to get too ahead of yourself.

202
00:12:42,257 --> 00:12:43,849
- Bruce.
- I got to go!

203
00:12:43,937 --> 00:12:47,054
- They're calling me in.
- OK, honey. Good luck. I love you.

204
00:12:49,257 --> 00:12:50,770
Let's do it.

205
00:12:51,017 --> 00:12:54,726
- They want you close to the falls.
- I'm going to get soaked.

206
00:12:54,817 --> 00:12:57,285
That's the point.
They want you to put this on.

207
00:12:57,377 --> 00:13:00,335
Part of the condition
of us getting the exclusive.

208
00:13:00,417 --> 00:13:04,330
You know what?
Nothing can bother me today. Nothing.

209
00:13:04,417 --> 00:13:07,932
Now remember,
it's their 156th-year anniversary.

210
00:13:08,017 --> 00:13:11,896
149 capacity. They cater
to tourists, honeymooners...

211
00:13:11,977 --> 00:13:14,730
And people who are insanely thirsty.
I get it.

212
00:13:14,817 --> 00:13:17,331
You're going to interview
Irene Dansfield.

213
00:13:17,417 --> 00:13:21,410
Irene, a pleasure to meet you.
You look beautiful.

214
00:13:21,497 --> 00:13:23,772
Irene's mother rode on the maiden voyage.

215
00:13:23,857 --> 00:13:25,688
- Rub that in my face!
- 90 seconds!

216
00:13:25,777 --> 00:13:27,210
Holy hell.

217
00:13:29,457 --> 00:13:31,413
Because of the fast response,

218
00:13:31,497 --> 00:13:35,376
the chemicals were cleaned up
without incident. Susan?

219
00:13:35,457 --> 00:13:37,607
Bruce Nolan is at Niagara Falls.

220
00:13:37,697 --> 00:13:40,894
But before we go live to Bruce,
we have an announcement.

221
00:13:40,977 --> 00:13:43,411
As everyone knows, after 33 years,

222
00:13:43,497 --> 00:13:46,728
our beloved Pete Fineman is retiring.

223
00:13:46,817 --> 00:13:51,288
Pete's shoes are virtually impossible
to fill, but the show must go on.

224
00:13:51,377 --> 00:13:56,656
And we could think ofno one better
than our very own Evan Baxter.

225
00:13:59,017 --> 00:14:00,052
Oh, boy!

226
00:14:00,457 --> 00:14:03,051
- Congratulations.
- I'm thrilled and honoured.

227
00:14:03,137 --> 00:14:07,528
As you said, no one can replace
Pete, but I will do my best.

228
00:14:07,617 --> 00:14:12,088
I am so proud to be a part
of our local community of Buffalo.

229
00:14:12,177 --> 00:14:17,092
I think, in a lot of ways, a great
city is like a great recipe, really.

230
00:14:17,177 --> 00:14:20,567
You take hard-working citizens,
add some care-givers,

231
00:14:20,657 --> 00:14:22,409
maybe a few nuts!

232
00:14:25,577 --> 00:14:29,172
All sprinkled with the love
and support of our good families.

233
00:14:29,257 --> 00:14:33,170
Ultimately, that makes
one sweet place to live.

234
00:14:33,577 --> 00:14:36,649
- That was amazing.
- I wish I'd written something.

235
00:14:36,737 --> 00:14:40,252
And now let's go live to that wacky
Bruce Nolan at Niagara Falls.

236
00:14:40,337 --> 00:14:42,009
Hey, wacky Bruce!

237
00:14:46,217 --> 00:14:49,368
- Talk, Bruce. Hello.
- Talk, honey.

238
00:14:49,457 --> 00:14:51,254
- What's going on?
- A Walt Disney.

239
00:14:51,337 --> 00:14:53,692
- It's frozen solid.
- Check the feed.

240
00:14:53,777 --> 00:14:55,893
We may be having technical difficulty.

241
00:14:55,977 --> 00:14:57,854
- The feed's good, Jack.
- Come on.

242
00:14:57,937 --> 00:15:01,566
- Talk, Bruce, damn it.
- Get ready to pull the plug.

243
00:15:01,657 --> 00:15:04,046
Come on, baby. Say something!

244
00:15:04,417 --> 00:15:06,135
Bruce, talk.

245
00:15:09,017 --> 00:15:10,655
- Hi, Susan.
- Thank you, God.

246
00:15:10,737 --> 00:15:12,056
Bruce Nolan here,

247
00:15:12,137 --> 00:15:15,573
aboard the Maid Of The Mist
in fabulous Niagara Falls, New York.

248
00:15:16,217 --> 00:15:20,210
First, let me just add another
congratulations to Evan Backstabber.

249
00:15:20,297 --> 00:15:22,447
Pardon me, Bastard... Baxter.

250
00:15:22,537 --> 00:15:25,335
It is good to see what
someone with real talent can do

251
00:15:25,417 --> 00:15:28,568
when great opportunities
are given to them instead of me.

252
00:15:29,977 --> 00:15:32,889
Anyway, I'm here
with Katharine Hepburn's mom.

253
00:15:32,977 --> 00:15:37,528
Why did you throw the Heart of the Ocean
jewel over the railing of the Titanic?

254
00:15:38,177 --> 00:15:40,532
Did you feel bad
letting Leo DiCaprio drown

255
00:15:40,617 --> 00:15:42,926
while you were safe
floating on the door?

256
00:15:43,017 --> 00:15:44,530
Could you have taken turns?

257
00:15:44,617 --> 00:15:47,973
Or were you too afraid
to freeze your big fat ass off?

258
00:15:49,097 --> 00:15:50,769
I guess that's how life is.

259
00:15:50,857 --> 00:15:55,214
Some people are drenched, freezing
on a stupid boat with a stupid hat,

260
00:15:55,297 --> 00:15:58,494
while others are in a news studio,
sucking up the glory.

261
00:15:58,577 --> 00:16:00,568
Oh, well. No big deal.

262
00:16:01,897 --> 00:16:05,287
The owner of the Maid Of The Mist.
Let's have a talk with him.

263
00:16:05,377 --> 00:16:08,255
Come on in here, Bill.
No, let's have a talk.

264
00:16:08,337 --> 00:16:10,248
What are you doing?

265
00:16:10,337 --> 00:16:13,409
You've been running
the Maid Of The Mistfor 23 years.

266
00:16:13,497 --> 00:16:15,533
Why do you think
I didn't get anchor?

267
00:16:15,617 --> 00:16:18,051
- I don't want any problems.
- Is it my hair?

268
00:16:18,137 --> 00:16:21,254
Are my teeth not white enough?
Or, like the great falls,

269
00:16:21,337 --> 00:16:26,286
is the bedrock of my life
eroding beneath me?

270
00:16:26,377 --> 00:16:31,527
Eroding!

271
00:16:32,977 --> 00:16:35,537
- Cut the feed. Go to black.
- I'm on it.

272
00:16:37,137 --> 00:16:40,891
I'm Bruce Nolan, for Eyewitness News.
Back to you, fuckers!

273
00:16:42,497 --> 00:16:44,089
- Oh, boy.
- Oh, my God.

274
00:16:48,857 --> 00:16:50,529
That is perfect.

275
00:16:50,617 --> 00:16:53,415
That is the motivation that I needed!

276
00:16:53,497 --> 00:16:55,567
Right there! Thank you!

277
00:16:56,977 --> 00:17:00,094
Thank you, WKBW.

278
00:17:00,177 --> 00:17:03,487
Wimpy... Kitty Baby Whiners!

279
00:17:03,577 --> 00:17:05,568
That's what that stands for!

280
00:17:07,137 --> 00:17:09,412
I'll see you on Channel 5.

281
00:17:09,497 --> 00:17:11,533
Where they do the real news!

282
00:17:12,777 --> 00:17:14,768
Do I look blind to you?

283
00:17:17,937 --> 00:17:19,893
Let's go, man. Come on.

284
00:17:20,617 --> 00:17:22,414
What are you doing?

285
00:17:22,497 --> 00:17:24,613
Come on. Leave the poor guy alone!

286
00:17:25,537 --> 00:17:27,687
You OK, man?

287
00:17:28,897 --> 00:17:30,808
Yeah, you better keep walking.

288
00:17:31,137 --> 00:17:34,174
- What'd you say, ese?
- Run, man!

289
00:17:34,257 --> 00:17:36,248
Run!

290
00:17:37,217 --> 00:17:39,253
Oh, God!

291
00:17:41,417 --> 00:17:43,328
OK, I didn't mean it!

292
00:17:43,857 --> 00:17:46,735
- I was just kidding!
- Hey, you forgot your things.

293
00:17:51,257 --> 00:17:53,248
Say something now!

294
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:59,415
B- E-A...

295
00:18:00,497 --> 00:18:02,806
.. utiful.

296
00:18:06,137 --> 00:18:08,605
That's what I get...

297
00:18:08,697 --> 00:18:11,609
That's what I get
for trying to help someone.

298
00:18:13,537 --> 00:18:15,892
Don't look at me, Walter.

299
00:18:15,977 --> 00:18:17,968
Oh, no!

300
00:18:22,017 --> 00:18:24,008
That's my payment, I guess.

301
00:18:24,097 --> 00:18:26,406
That is my reward.

302
00:18:31,217 --> 00:18:34,493
Just? Just get a clue!

303
00:18:35,737 --> 00:18:37,329
Thank God you're all right.

304
00:18:37,417 --> 00:18:39,533
God, yeah. Let's thank God.

305
00:18:39,617 --> 00:18:42,256
For his blessings
are raining down upon me.

306
00:18:42,337 --> 00:18:45,249
- Wait! That's not rain!
- Bruce, please don't do that.

307
00:18:45,337 --> 00:18:47,851
Everything happens for a reason.

308
00:18:47,937 --> 00:18:51,009
That I don't need. That is a cliché.
That is not helpful.

309
00:18:51,097 --> 00:18:53,565
"A bird in the hand
is worth two in the bush. "

310
00:18:53,657 --> 00:18:56,569
I have no bird! No bush!
God has taken my bird and my bush.

311
00:18:56,657 --> 00:18:59,694
I see. So God is picking on you?

312
00:18:59,777 --> 00:19:02,086
No! He's ignoring me completely.

313
00:19:03,097 --> 00:19:05,531
He's busy giving Evan
everything he wants.

314
00:19:06,617 --> 00:19:09,654
Great, Sam. But you missed
your target. I'm over here!

315
00:19:09,737 --> 00:19:12,012
Don't get mad at the dog.
It's not his fault.

316
00:19:12,097 --> 00:19:15,214
It's God's fault.
He gave him the wrong co-ordinates.

317
00:19:15,297 --> 00:19:17,731
Enough!
Will you stop being such a martyr?

318
00:19:17,817 --> 00:19:20,251
I am not being a martyr! I'm a victim!

319
00:19:20,337 --> 00:19:24,091
God is a mean kid with
a magniying glass, and I'm the ant.

320
00:19:24,177 --> 00:19:26,293
He could fix my life if he wanted,

321
00:19:26,377 --> 00:19:29,574
but he'd rather burn off my feelers
and watch me squirm.

322
00:19:29,657 --> 00:19:31,932
Sweetheart, I know you're mad.

323
00:19:32,017 --> 00:19:35,407
What Evan did was slimy and wrong.

324
00:19:35,497 --> 00:19:38,807
This day could have been so
much worse. I'm just glad you're OK.

325
00:19:39,017 --> 00:19:42,248
OK? News flash! I'm not OK.

326
00:19:42,337 --> 00:19:45,693
I'm not OK with a mediocre job!
Or a mediocre apartment!

327
00:19:45,777 --> 00:19:48,337
I'm not OK with a mediocre life!

328
00:19:56,497 --> 00:19:59,489
Is that what you think we have?
A mediocre life?

329
00:19:59,577 --> 00:20:01,488
Don't make this about you.

330
00:20:01,577 --> 00:20:05,013
About me?
How could I make this about me?

331
00:20:05,097 --> 00:20:08,214
It's about you. It's always about you.

332
00:20:08,297 --> 00:20:10,527
Perfect.

333
00:20:10,617 --> 00:20:14,895
I'll have the worst day of my life
with a side order of guilt, please!

334
00:20:20,377 --> 00:20:23,767
OK, God. You want me to talk to you?

335
00:20:24,217 --> 00:20:27,015
Then talk back.
Tell me what's going on.

336
00:20:27,097 --> 00:20:29,895
What should I do? Give me a signal.

337
00:20:32,297 --> 00:20:36,085
I need your guidance, Lord.
Please, send me a sign.

338
00:20:40,017 --> 00:20:42,008
Oh, what's this joker doing now?

339
00:20:47,537 --> 00:20:50,290
OK. All right. I'll try it your way.

340
00:20:51,057 --> 00:20:55,767
All right. Lord... I need a miracle.

341
00:20:57,097 --> 00:20:58,769
I'm desperate.

342
00:20:58,857 --> 00:21:00,529
I need your help, Lord.

343
00:21:00,617 --> 00:21:02,847
Please, reach into my life...

344
00:21:05,577 --> 00:21:08,045
What the...? Where are you?

345
00:21:08,137 --> 00:21:10,128
Got you!

346
00:21:51,537 --> 00:21:52,856
Fine!

347
00:21:52,937 --> 00:21:54,814
The gloves are off, pal!

348
00:21:54,897 --> 00:21:57,252
Come on! Let me see a little wrath!

349
00:21:57,337 --> 00:22:01,012
Smite me, O mighty smiter!

350
00:22:01,857 --> 00:22:04,166
You're the one who should be fired!

351
00:22:04,257 --> 00:22:08,569
The only one around here
not doing his job is you!

352
00:22:09,577 --> 00:22:11,568
Answer me!

353
00:22:25,977 --> 00:22:27,968
Sorry. Don't know you.

354
00:22:28,937 --> 00:22:30,928
Wouldn't call you if I did.

355
00:22:43,217 --> 00:22:45,208
Oh, God!

356
00:22:51,497 --> 00:22:53,931
Hello, 5550123.

357
00:23:17,337 --> 00:23:21,296
Oh, no! Sam, this has got to stop!

358
00:23:23,777 --> 00:23:27,292
Get it straight. That's the house.
This is the bathroom.

359
00:23:27,377 --> 00:23:31,336
House, bathroom. Bathroom, house.

360
00:23:33,817 --> 00:23:35,535
What's the point?

361
00:23:59,057 --> 00:24:01,696
5550123.

362
00:24:04,177 --> 00:24:06,975
Denied thatpromotion?
Is life unfair?

363
00:24:07,057 --> 00:24:10,174
Is someone less talented than you
reaping the benefits?

364
00:24:10,257 --> 00:24:11,815
Is yourname Bruce?

365
00:24:11,897 --> 00:24:13,967
Then do we have thejob foryou!

366
00:24:14,057 --> 00:24:17,288
We're located at 7725623rd Street.

367
00:24:17,377 --> 00:24:20,687
So come on down -
or we'lljust keep beeping you.

368
00:24:37,097 --> 00:24:38,496
"Omni Presents. "

369
00:24:39,857 --> 00:24:43,008
Oh, yeah. The glass is half-full.

370
00:24:46,497 --> 00:24:49,409
Come on! Look! What is that?

371
00:24:54,737 --> 00:24:56,170
Thank you again.

372
00:25:03,737 --> 00:25:05,728
What the...?

373
00:25:12,537 --> 00:25:14,528
You're looking for room 7.

374
00:25:16,897 --> 00:25:19,934
- Yeah, I figured.
- Want me to even those up for you?

375
00:25:24,497 --> 00:25:27,534
- How do I get to room 7?
- That'd be on the 7th floor.

376
00:25:27,617 --> 00:25:31,087
- Stairs are over there.
- I'll take the elevator.

377
00:25:31,177 --> 00:25:34,692
- Out of order.
- The stairs were my second choice.

378
00:25:34,777 --> 00:25:37,371
Do you mind giving me a hand
with this floor?

379
00:25:37,457 --> 00:25:41,211
What? That's good.

380
00:25:41,297 --> 00:25:42,730
Are you serious?

381
00:25:44,977 --> 00:25:47,537
I'm kind of busy. Rain check.

382
00:25:48,777 --> 00:25:50,529
I'll hold you to it.

383
00:25:51,137 --> 00:25:53,731
I'm free on the 7th at 7.00.

384
00:25:56,897 --> 00:25:58,888
The 7th at 7.00 it is.

385
00:26:01,817 --> 00:26:04,092
This looks promising.

386
00:26:09,137 --> 00:26:11,048
Hello?

387
00:26:11,137 --> 00:26:14,527
Another hugantic,
ginormic waste of my life.

388
00:26:15,697 --> 00:26:17,688
Hello?

389
00:26:18,497 --> 00:26:20,692
I'm looking for whoever runs this joint!

390
00:26:20,777 --> 00:26:23,371
Be right with you. I'm fixing a light.

391
00:26:23,457 --> 00:26:25,527
Tell me if it's working.

392
00:26:25,617 --> 00:26:27,687
Yeah. Seems to be.

393
00:26:27,777 --> 00:26:31,565
- Kind of bright, though.
- Yeah. It is for most people.

394
00:26:31,657 --> 00:26:35,809
Spend their lives in the dark,
trying to hide from me.

395
00:26:37,417 --> 00:26:39,487
The elevator's broken, huh?

396
00:26:39,577 --> 00:26:42,489
Yeah, but I'll get around to it.

397
00:26:43,737 --> 00:26:47,412
- You installed a clapper?
- No, but catchy jingle, isn't it?

398
00:26:48,097 --> 00:26:49,769
Clap on, clap off

399
00:26:51,177 --> 00:26:52,849
The clapper

400
00:26:53,737 --> 00:26:56,171
Just can't get it out of my head.

401
00:26:56,257 --> 00:26:58,532
Well, good luck with that.

402
00:26:58,617 --> 00:27:00,369
- I'm going to go now.
- OK.

403
00:27:00,457 --> 00:27:02,652
But the boss will be right out.

404
00:27:10,337 --> 00:27:14,455
You must be Bruce.
I've been expecting you.

405
00:27:16,657 --> 00:27:18,409
This is hilarious.

406
00:27:18,497 --> 00:27:21,136
You're the boss,
electrician and janitor.

407
00:27:21,217 --> 00:27:23,128
Must be a killer Christmas party.

408
00:27:23,217 --> 00:27:26,527
Don't get drunk, though.
One of you might need a ride home.

409
00:27:27,857 --> 00:27:31,088
You always were funny, Bruce.
Just like your father.

410
00:27:31,937 --> 00:27:34,610
He didn't mind
rolling up his sleeves either.

411
00:27:34,697 --> 00:27:39,373
People underestimate the benefit of
manual labour. There's freedom in it.

412
00:27:39,457 --> 00:27:43,496
Some of the happiest people smell to
high heaven at the end of the day.

413
00:27:44,497 --> 00:27:46,533
All right, what is this?

414
00:27:46,657 --> 00:27:49,535
How do you know my father
and how did you get my number?

415
00:27:49,617 --> 00:27:51,335
I know a lot about you, Bruce.

416
00:27:52,777 --> 00:27:55,086
Just about everything there is to know.

417
00:27:56,017 --> 00:28:00,647
Everything you've ever said or done
or thought about doing.

418
00:28:01,617 --> 00:28:04,211
Right there in that file cabinet.

419
00:28:04,897 --> 00:28:08,333
- Wow! A whole drawer, just for me.
- Yeah.

420
00:28:08,417 --> 00:28:10,806
Mind if I take a look?

421
00:28:10,897 --> 00:28:13,331
It's your life.

422
00:28:13,417 --> 00:28:15,408
This oughta be good.

423
00:28:29,137 --> 00:28:31,412
This last entry was a little disturbing.

424
00:28:43,177 --> 00:28:45,133
"The gloves are off, God. "

425
00:28:45,217 --> 00:28:47,685
"God has taken my bird and my bush. "

426
00:28:47,777 --> 00:28:51,053
"God is a mean kid
with a magniying glass. "

427
00:28:51,137 --> 00:28:54,288
"Smite me, O mighty smiter. "

428
00:28:54,377 --> 00:28:58,290
I'm not much for blaspheming,
but that last one made me laugh.

429
00:28:58,377 --> 00:29:00,368
Are you spying on me?

430
00:29:03,697 --> 00:29:06,165
Who are you?

431
00:29:06,257 --> 00:29:08,248
I am the One.

432
00:29:08,337 --> 00:29:11,454
Creator of the heavens and the earth.
Alpha and Omega.

433
00:29:12,817 --> 00:29:15,092
I see where this is going.

434
00:29:15,177 --> 00:29:17,850
Bruce... I am God.

435
00:29:17,937 --> 00:29:19,893
Bingo! Yahtzee!

436
00:29:19,977 --> 00:29:23,936
Is that your final answer?
Our survey says, "God!"

437
00:29:25,577 --> 00:29:27,329
It was nice to meet you, God.

438
00:29:27,417 --> 00:29:30,887
Thanks for the Grand Canyon.
Good luck with the Apocalypse.

439
00:29:30,977 --> 00:29:34,287
And by the way, you suck!

440
00:29:34,377 --> 00:29:36,333
It would have been more impressive

441
00:29:36,417 --> 00:29:39,375
if you hadn't used
the cheesy file cabinet illusion.

442
00:29:39,457 --> 00:29:42,130
Anybody with a brain stem
can tell that drawer

443
00:29:42,217 --> 00:29:44,811
is being fed through the wall
from the other side.

444
00:29:44,897 --> 00:29:47,809
All you have to do
is find the crease right around here.

445
00:29:47,897 --> 00:29:51,173
There is a seam here, or a hollow spot.

446
00:29:55,777 --> 00:29:57,608
Where?

447
00:29:57,697 --> 00:29:59,688
Through the dry wall and concrete?

448
00:30:02,617 --> 00:30:05,495
OK, that is a good one.

449
00:30:06,177 --> 00:30:10,455
- How many fingers am I holding up?
- Thou shalt not tempt the Lord.

450
00:30:10,537 --> 00:30:12,368
- If you can't do it...
- Three.

451
00:30:12,457 --> 00:30:14,448
Two... four... nine.

452
00:30:14,537 --> 00:30:16,289
Six... eight... one.

453
00:30:18,697 --> 00:30:20,096
OK.

454
00:30:20,857 --> 00:30:22,654
How many now?

455
00:30:22,737 --> 00:30:24,011
Seven.

456
00:30:28,857 --> 00:30:32,486
- How?
- You've been complaining about me.

457
00:30:32,577 --> 00:30:35,535
- I'm tired of it.
- Don't come near me. Seriously.

458
00:30:35,617 --> 00:30:38,654
I don't want to hurt you,
but I will out of instinct.

459
00:30:38,737 --> 00:30:42,446
You haven't won a fight since
grade 5, and that was against a girl.

460
00:30:44,017 --> 00:30:46,690
But she was huge.
She'd been held back.

461
00:30:46,777 --> 00:30:48,847
And the sun was in your eyes.

462
00:30:48,937 --> 00:30:50,814
Ah, the ego.

463
00:30:50,897 --> 00:30:53,457
Anyway, I brought you here
to offer you a job.

464
00:30:53,537 --> 00:30:56,051
- A job? What job?
- My job.

465
00:30:56,137 --> 00:30:59,334
You think you can do it better,
so here's your chance.

466
00:30:59,417 --> 00:31:03,376
When you leave this building,
you will be endowed with all my powers.

467
00:31:04,297 --> 00:31:06,174
Sure. Whatever you say, pal.

468
00:31:09,217 --> 00:31:12,926
OK. That did not happen.
No one needs to hear about it.

469
00:31:13,017 --> 00:31:15,008
I'm deleting the program.

470
00:31:16,697 --> 00:31:18,335
No.

471
00:31:18,417 --> 00:31:20,214
I'm having a breakdown.

472
00:31:20,297 --> 00:31:23,767
Everyday psychotic episode,
caused by a tumour, a brain lesion.

473
00:31:24,657 --> 00:31:26,568
Come on. Start!

474
00:31:28,537 --> 00:31:30,528
That was lucky.

475
00:31:34,977 --> 00:31:36,854
Come on. Calm down.

476
00:31:36,937 --> 00:31:39,735
You did not meet God.
You do not have his powers.

477
00:31:40,457 --> 00:31:42,732
If that was God, I'm Clint Eastwood.

478
00:31:42,817 --> 00:31:44,808
Holy hell!

479
00:31:50,297 --> 00:31:53,209
Be careful what you wish for, punk.

480
00:31:53,617 --> 00:31:55,096
Nope!

481
00:31:56,457 --> 00:32:00,052
I am a reasonable,
sane human being.

482
00:32:00,137 --> 00:32:01,889
With a. 44 Magnum.

483
00:32:01,977 --> 00:32:04,286
The most powerful handgun in the...

484
00:32:05,257 --> 00:32:09,045
I'm not Clint Eastwood.
I'm Bruce Nolan.

485
00:32:09,137 --> 00:32:11,128
I'm Bruce Nolan!

486
00:32:24,737 --> 00:32:26,728
That was not real.

487
00:32:28,697 --> 00:32:31,336
- Coffee?
- Coffee, yeah.

488
00:32:31,417 --> 00:32:33,328
We have a special on soup today.

489
00:32:33,417 --> 00:32:37,410
- No, thank you.
- It's tomato. I made it myself.

490
00:32:38,817 --> 00:32:40,409
OK.

491
00:33:13,137 --> 00:33:15,128
Excuse me, I need a spoo-...

492
00:33:22,057 --> 00:33:24,048
It's OK. I found one.

493
00:33:31,137 --> 00:33:32,855
