1062
01:20:26,737 --> 01:20:29,046
You know what I do before I go to bed?

1063
01:20:29,137 --> 01:20:32,812
I tuck my kids in, maybe have
some ice cream and watch Conan.

1064
01:20:34,577 --> 01:20:36,568
Know what Grace does?

1065
01:20:37,737 --> 01:20:39,728
She prays.

1066
01:20:40,857 --> 01:20:42,609
Most of the time for you.

1067
01:21:03,697 --> 01:21:06,928
Find Grace Connelly.

1068
01:21:09,657 --> 01:21:11,648
The woman does pray a lot.

1069
01:21:13,617 --> 01:21:16,211
Find... Grace and Bruce.

1070
01:21:17,337 --> 01:21:19,646
"Dear God,
please help Bruce find himself,

1071
01:21:19,737 --> 01:21:21,693
find contentment, find you. "

1072
01:21:21,777 --> 01:21:25,213
"Dear God, please help Bruce.
He seems to be struggling. "

1073
01:21:25,297 --> 01:21:27,253
"Dear God, give Bruce strength. "

1074
01:21:27,337 --> 01:21:29,055
"Dear God, bless Bruce. "

1075
01:21:33,737 --> 01:21:35,568
It's her.

1076
01:21:36,137 --> 01:21:39,288
Sammy, she's logging on.
She's praying right now.

1077
01:21:46,297 --> 01:21:48,015
Please, God.

1078
01:21:49,577 --> 01:21:50,896
Please.

1079
01:21:50,977 --> 01:21:52,933
I still love him.

1080
01:21:55,257 --> 01:21:58,135
But I don't want to love him any more.

1081
01:21:58,217 --> 01:22:00,606
I don't want to hurt any more. Please.

1082
01:22:01,217 --> 01:22:03,208
Help me forget.

1083
01:22:03,937 --> 01:22:05,928
Please help me to let it go.

1084
01:22:07,057 --> 01:22:09,287
Please help me let him go.

1085
01:22:29,537 --> 01:22:31,528
You win!

1086
01:22:32,217 --> 01:22:34,014
I'm done!

1087
01:22:34,097 --> 01:22:37,772
Please! I don't want to do this any more!

1088
01:22:38,697 --> 01:22:40,688
I don't want to be God.

1089
01:22:41,297 --> 01:22:44,653
I want you to decide
what's right for me!

1090
01:22:44,737 --> 01:22:47,456
I surrender to your will!

1091
01:23:16,497 --> 01:23:17,816
Am I...?

1092
01:23:17,897 --> 01:23:21,731
You can't kneel down in the middle
of a highway and live to talk about it.

1093
01:23:21,817 --> 01:23:23,808
But why?

1094
01:23:25,017 --> 01:23:26,609
Why now?

1095
01:23:26,697 --> 01:23:28,289
Bruce...

1096
01:23:29,177 --> 01:23:31,896
you have the divine spark.

1097
01:23:31,977 --> 01:23:35,765
You have the gift for bringing joy
and laughter to the world.

1098
01:23:36,857 --> 01:23:38,848
I know. I created you.

1099
01:23:40,217 --> 01:23:42,492
- Quit bragging.
- See?

1100
01:23:42,577 --> 01:23:44,772
That's what I'm talking about.

1101
01:23:44,857 --> 01:23:46,848
That's the spark.

1102
01:23:51,497 --> 01:23:53,613
What do you want me to do?

1103
01:23:54,577 --> 01:23:56,408
I want you to pray, son.

1104
01:23:56,897 --> 01:24:00,014
Go ahead. Use them.

1105
01:24:05,577 --> 01:24:08,614
Lord, feed the hungry.

1106
01:24:08,697 --> 01:24:11,973
And bring peace to...

1107
01:24:13,417 --> 01:24:15,408
all of mankind.

1108
01:24:17,377 --> 01:24:19,572
- How's that?
- Great.

1109
01:24:19,657 --> 01:24:22,330
If you want to be Miss America.

1110
01:24:22,417 --> 01:24:25,853
Now, come on.
What do you really care about?

1111
01:24:30,177 --> 01:24:32,452
Grace.

1112
01:24:35,217 --> 01:24:37,208
You want her back?

1113
01:24:41,457 --> 01:24:43,448
No.

1114
01:24:44,537 --> 01:24:46,528
I want her to be happy.

1115
01:24:48,777 --> 01:24:51,132
No matter what that means.

1116
01:24:51,217 --> 01:24:53,412
I want her to find someone

1117
01:24:53,497 --> 01:24:55,488
who'll treat her

1118
01:24:56,377 --> 01:25:00,973
with all the love she deserved from me.

1119
01:25:03,497 --> 01:25:05,488
I want her to meet someone

1120
01:25:10,577 --> 01:25:12,568
who'll see her always

1121
01:25:13,697 --> 01:25:15,688
as I do now.

1122
01:25:20,137 --> 01:25:22,253
Through your eyes.

1123
01:25:22,857 --> 01:25:25,530
- Now that's a prayer.
- Yeah?

1124
01:25:26,577 --> 01:25:29,887
Yeah. It's good.

1125
01:25:34,897 --> 01:25:37,013
I'm going to get right on it.

1126
01:25:37,817 --> 01:25:39,694
Clear!

1127
01:25:39,777 --> 01:25:42,132
That didn't feel very good.

1128
01:25:43,057 --> 01:25:45,810
- Got a rhythm.
- I got a pulse.

1129
01:25:45,897 --> 01:25:48,855
- Let's get him up.
- Get the backboard and brace.

1130
01:25:59,057 --> 01:26:01,013
Welcome back.

1131
01:26:01,097 --> 01:26:03,213
You're lucky to be alive, son.

1132
01:26:03,297 --> 01:26:05,288
Someone up there must like you.

1133
01:26:19,977 --> 01:26:24,095
I hear all that stuff winds up
in a warehouse somewhere.

1134
01:26:29,657 --> 01:26:31,648
Hi, baby.

1135
01:26:33,417 --> 01:26:36,966
Oh, my God, look at you.

1136
01:26:37,377 --> 01:26:40,335
- I was such an idiot.
- It's OK.

1137
01:26:47,377 --> 01:26:50,130
I don't know what I would have done.

1138
01:26:50,937 --> 01:26:55,328
Oh, God. I swear I wanted
to be mad at you forever.

1139
01:27:06,777 --> 01:27:08,768
Now you're just showing off.

1140
01:27:19,817 --> 01:27:23,696
This is Bruce Nolan here at Buffalo's
first "Be the Miracle" blood drive.

1141
01:27:23,777 --> 01:27:26,575
It's a B-E-A-utiful day.

1142
01:27:26,657 --> 01:27:29,933
So come on down,
because the life you save could be mine.

1143
01:27:30,337 --> 01:27:35,092
